cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and their virtualization. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the proposed architecture involves sharing resources/infrastructure by multiple independent entities. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a novel architecture for WSN virtualization. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may involve discussing the algorithms used in the proposed architecture. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may involve discussing the software design and implementation of the proposed architecture.
